The paper discusses the analysis of network structures from complex and noisy data, which is a common problem in various fields of computer science. The paper specifically mentions empirical studies of networks in the Internet, World Wide Web, biological systems, and social networks, indicating that it could belong to several sub-categories. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on social networks and their structures. 

cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper mentions the use of techniques to estimate network structures from data in arbitrary formats, which could include sound and control systems. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible categories as the paper discusses the use of techniques to make optimal estimates of network structures from noisy and incomplete data, which could involve data structures and machine learning algorithms.
